        "content": "<p>Note also that Patrick's tactic proof literally just reads the terms in <code>λ x₁ x₂ h, injf (injg h)</code>, in that order, so it is just literally building the function piece by piece. This is why the \"backwards\" argument (using injectivity of <code>f</code> before injectivity of <code>g</code>) is so natural to computer scientists, because that's how they build the function.</p>",
